{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Spread desiccated coconut over a dry frying pan and toast over a low heat, stirring frequently, until golden brown. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Using the same frying pan, toast coriander seeds, dried chilli flakes, black peppercorns, cumin seeds, dried fennel seeds, cinnamon stick, cloves and star anise for 5 minutes.","Add poppy seeds and toast for a further 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Transfer toasted spices to bowl with coconut and leave to cool for 15 minutes.","Place 45 g water, garlic and cooled toasted spices in mixing bowl then blend <nobr>30 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add 45 g water and blend again <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> to a thick xacuti paste. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place onions and oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Sauté <nobr>12 min\/90°C\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Add reserved xacuti paste and fry <nobr>5 min\/90°C\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Add paprika and 50 g water then cook <nobr>5 min\/95°C\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Add remaining 300 g water and boil <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Add prawns and cook <nobr>3 min\/95°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add nutmeg and tamarind paste then simmer <nobr>5 min\/90°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Serve hot, sprinkled with chopped fresh coriander."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["120 g desiccated coconut","2 Tbsp coriander seeds","2 tsp dried chilli flakes","1 tsp black peppercorns","1 tsp cumin seeds","1 tsp dried fennel seeds","1 cinnamon stick","4 cloves","2 star anise","1 Tbsp poppy seeds","440 g water","4 garlic cloves","200 g onions, quartered","25 g vegetable oil","1 ¼ tsp paprika","300 - 400 g peeled, raw prawns","½ tsp ground nutmeg","3 Tbsp tamarind paste","5 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only, chopped, for garnish"]}],"id":"r109901","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-LIqbS4uW2po\/XZVPGtMeWiI\/AAAAAAAAc08\/7AGhzOd72QMBofNf2HvxmXvhbEHL2agrwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_04jHaw2UsVATQrl0.png","title":"Prawn Xacuti","publishedAt":"2017-04-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17.4 g","fat":"28.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"19.6 g","calories":"1686 kJ \/ 403 kcal"},"usefulItems":"non-stick frying pan, hob","hintsAndTricks":["We go back to South India for this traditional curry. Pronounced ‘shakooti’, this dish has a unique flavour and aroma. The beautiful red colour comes from roasting the coconut and spices first.","For a thinner sauce, add an extra 50 g water in step 9."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 20m","4 portions"]}